caption: I was taken aback today. I’ve always enjoyed my fresh salads but today I ordered my salad but instead of receiving a full salad I got 3/4 of a bowl. By the time my salad dressing was added it was much less. I asked to put more “lettuce”- “lettuce” in my bowl and the Server stated that she could not. I asked to speak with the manager and she said it is now their  policy to serve less for the same price! WTW the manger Jessica wasn’t helpful at all. She stated that it’s the company policy and oh well if ‘you’ don’t like it! WTW NEVER GOING BACK and I plan to let my colleagues know to go other places for lunch! Very disappointed!! Doesn’t deserve a STAR. In addition the stations were very messy. I had to ask them to clean around it before something  fell in my bowl.
Everytime I come here I'm underwhelmed. The food is mediocre, but the staff act like they've never made a sandwich before. And it's pricey to boot.

This place is very low in quality, the food is always cold and has lost its bad feeling costumer service, they can not make a simple change of bread without putting attitude the quality and taste of the food is totally poor

I really liked this place when it first opened, especially the breakfast menu. However, I went in today and the service was poor; my breakfast sandwich was awful, the bacon was under cooked, raw, really, the egg was overcooked, even though I was asked how I wanted my egg, and they were out of brioche buns, the wheat bread substitute was not toasted and the cheese and toppings, grilled shallots, spicy sauce, were very skimpy. I also had a salad a few weeks ago and the greens, kale, were gritty.
Food is great, gets very busy during lunch hours and can get a little chaotic

I am a frequent customer in Vienna but today I decided to stop at this new location and I loved it, the food is delicious I do not know if it is a new concept, perfectly cooked steak and flavored I could enjoy every bite congratulations to the chef Love it, my new favorite place in DC
Great place to eat , I stop pass here almost everyday. Mariah is a great employee you need more like her. She’s very polite and make sure she suggest something new for me to try every time.

Excellent process (large lines move fast), excellent food selection (lots of reasonably healthy options with or without meats), and friendly service all down the line. Fairly priced with serving sizes that justify the cost. I definitely recommend this place if you want to eat "clean", light, and feel full when finished.

Delicious, quick stop for a healthy lunch.  Have had nothing but great meals here.  Staff is very nice and helpful while Arita (owner) went above and beyond to ensure everything was fresh and tasty.  Recommend to anyone looking for a business lunch and definitely way better quality than Sweet Green or Chopt.
The manager gave me attitude because I wanted to pay both in cash and debit card. I mean I didn’t think I was a big deal but for her it was for her I guess jeezzz

I work right upstairs from this place.  The service is great, everyone is nice and helpful.  Food is delicious and portions are HUGE.  Great price value over the old Bean & Bite that was here previously.  Recommend the kabobi rice bowl (no changes) and really any the sandwiches.  Get the sweet leaf app which has a reward system that is basically 10% off.
